"n.脾气暴躁之人 【英】 n. 脾气暴躁之人(a surly, ill-mannered, bad-tempered person) 【考】 反义词：agreeable person(随和的人) 【记】 无词根；分割记忆：c ur(可看作词根：跑)+ mud(泥)→跑到泥巴里 去→发脾气→脾气暴躁的人 n. (满怀怨恨而且顽固的)脾气暴躁的人 【记】cur跑, mud泥: 跑到泥巴里去－脾气暴躁的人cur流氓, mud妈的, geon真: 真他mud流氓－脾气暴躁的人读: cur痲疹, 出痲疹是因为脾气暴躁 【反】agreeable person(随和的人) 【记】cur + mud + go on 走到泥里的杂种狗一样，脾气坏，乱咬 curmudgeon (n.)  1570s, of unknown origin; the suggestion, based on a misreading of a garbled note from Johnson, that it is from French coeur mechant ""evil heart"" is not taken seriously; the first syllable may be cur ""dog."" Liberman says the word ""must have been borrowed from Gaelic (and references muigean ""disagreeable person""), with variant spelling of intensive prefix ker-. Related: Curmudgeonly."
